  "content": "<p>3\ufe0f\u20e31\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 31st post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>In v256 we added &quot;systemd-ssh-generator&quot;, which \u2013 among other things \u2013 would bind sshd to an AF_VSOCK socket if that is supported on the system, i.e. if booted inside a VMM that supports AF_VSOCK communication. It greatly simplifies talking to a VM from the host, in environments that support this.</p><p>Except of course, it&#39;s not quite as easy as it might appear conceptually:</p>",
